The paper deals with the edit distance problem, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and combinatorial pattern matching. The use of compression schemes to improve the time complexity of edit distance computation is a well-known technique, which suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of straight line programs to represent compression schemes, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents algorithms for computing edit distance under any rational scoring function, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category.
